<h2>HVAC Systems for San Antonio</h2>
<p>San Antonio's hot-humid climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling extreme heat while managing moisture levels effectively. The ideal HVAC system for San Antonio homes should have a SEER rating of at least 16, though systems with SEER 18-20 ratings provide optimal efficiency for the climate. Central air conditioning with variable-speed compressors performs exceptionally well in this environment, as they can adjust capacity based on demand while maintaining consistent humidity control throughout the cooling season.</p>

<p>Heat pump systems are increasingly popular in San Antonio due to their dual heating and cooling capabilities, though the heating function sees limited use given the mild winters. For optimal performance in the hot-humid climate, homeowners should prioritize systems with enhanced dehumidification features, properly sized ductwork, and programmable thermostats that can work in conjunction with solar panel systems to maximize energy savings during peak production hours.</p>

